Lets use reality as a guide here.
If I wish to send someone money. I ask that person "whats your Account(number)". Maybe we can slightly defiate from and just ask the economy plugin directly give me the account for `type:xyz`. I would even go as far as declaring `type` to a catalog type.
For players this would look like this `sponge:player:12334-1234-134...`
For those towns it could be `towny:town:my-awesome-city2k20`.
How the economy plugin stores those keys? We dont care. We also don't care whether the town returns a player account or a guild account or whatever.

The following code  is used to express my concept in more detail. It does not cover all aspects related to economy only the X -> account mapping. So please take it with a grain of salt.

