This PR adds a key bindings api that will allow plugin developers to create custom key bindings. The api is always available, on both client and server versions, this is because the server will send packets to register the key bindings on joining the server and cleaned up afterwards, but this is a implementation detail.

I am not sure if I should have waited for the client-phase-1, but since the client isn't required for players to join and the api impl does not require any client. The impl will only send packets to the client and recieve them back.

I am also also only going to implement this in the minecraft versions 1.9+, depending on which version should be supported at that time.

The implementation will follow once the api is mostly finished/reviewed.

Example usage:

``` java
private KeyBinding myTestKey;

@Listener
public void onGameInit(GameInitializationEvent event) {
    this.myTestKey = KeyBinding.builder()
            .id("testPluginId:test")
            .category(KeyCategories.GAMEPLAY)
            .build();
    Sponge.getRegistry().register(KeyBinding.class, this.myTestKey);
}

@Listener
public void onInteractKey(InteractKeyEvent event) {
    if (event.getKeyBinding() == this.myTestKey) {
        event.getTargetEntity().sendMessage(Text.of("Ow, that hurt..."));
    }
}
```

Networking draft:
Each key binding will have a internal id which will be used for networking, the default minecraft key bindings will get a inbuild internal id.

On Join:
1. Call the RegisterKeyBindingsEvent
2. Server -> Client: Register the custom key categories, includes string id, internal id and title
3. Server -> Client: Register the applicable custom key bindings, includes string id, internal id, name, category

While playing a player clicks/releases a key:
Client -> Server: Send state of the key

On logout:
Remove all the custom keys and categories.

